goal_info:
1 * road that does not end at the edge of the city.
-1 * road that ends at the edge of the city.

1 * each row & collumn with exactly 3 park blocks in it.
-3 * 1 * each row & collumn with exactly 0 park blocks in it.

1 * park blocks in your city.
-3* industrial blocks in your city.
-8 + 3 * groups of 4 "corner to corner" blocks of the same type. You may score multiple groups of the same type and a block may apply to more than one group. (max 7)
2 * industrial blocks adjecent to only commercial or industrial blocks
Subtract the number of blocks in your largest industrial group from the number of blocks in your largest residential group. score that many points

1 * parks located on the interior of the city
-2 * parks located on the edge of the city

1 * park blocks adjecent to your largest group of residential blocks.
-2 * industrial blocks adjecent to your largest group of residential blocks
1* industrial block that shares a corner with atleast 1 other industrial block
1 * commercial block in any 1 row or collumn of your choice. you may only score 1 row or collumn
2 * commercial block directly between two residential blocks with the same road connecting all three blocks. Blocks may be a straight line or in a stepped pattern
1 * every two road sections (rounded down) that are part of your longest road
3 * road that begins at one park and ends at a different park
1 * road section in a completed loop. You may score multiple loops in your city
2 * residential blocks adjecent to 2 or more industrial blocks
2* roads that passes through both a Residential block and a commercial block

1 * commercial block on the edge of the city.
1 * commercial block on a corner edge.
add the number of blocks in your longest row to the number of blocks in your longest column (skipping any gaps). score that many points
